+## Draft Replies
+
+### T-214-01
+Fixed. The fallback path in `src/policy/preview.py` now preserves both `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`, and `src/policy/approval_router.py` now normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before building the preview payload. The fallback regression is covered in `tests/test_preview.py`.
+
+### T-214-02
+Handled via the same fix as `T-214-01`. This thread is a duplicate of the reopened fallback payload regression, so there was no separate code path to change.
+
+### T-214-03
+Not applied. This suggestion points at an outdated hunk, and reviving a legacy preview branch on the current branch would reintroduce stale behavior rather than fix the reopened regression.
+
+### T-214-04
+Fixed. Added a regression test in `tests/test_preview.py` covering `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` and asserting the normalized fallback payload stays at `human_review_required` with `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+### T-214-05
+Fixed. Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example now includes the corrected `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` fields.
